5. Third Party Websites and
                        Frames
The Vivid Seats Marketplace includes links to other websites whose privacy practices may differ from those of Vivid Seats. If you submit personal information to any of those websites, or to any third parties, your information is governed by their privacy policies. In addition, some of our pages utilise framing techniques to serve content from our partners while preserving the look and feel of the Vivid Seats Marketplace. When we use framing techniques, we display the logo of our partner, so that you will know that you are engaging with a third party. Please be aware that you are providing your personal information to these third parties and not to www.vividseats.com, and the third parties’ privacy policy will govern their use of your information. We encourage you to carefully read the privacy policy of any other website you visit, and of any third parties to whom you provide personal information.
6. Security and Retention
We use Secure Socket Layers (“SSL”)
                    encryption technology through third-party providers where your personal and account information is
                    required (such as a credit card number).  All transaction information is processed under encrypted
                    channels.
We follow generally accepted industry standards to
                    protect your personal information, both during transmission and once we receive it. No method of
                    transmission over the Internet, or method of electronic storage, is 100% secure, however. Therefore,
                    while we strive to use commercially acceptable means to protect your personal information, we cannot
                    guarantee its absolute security.
We will keep your personal information only for as long as necessary for the purposes for which it was collected, to provide you with products or services, to carry out legitimate business interests, and where otherwise required or permitted by law. If you have any questions about security on the Vivid Seats Marketplace, you can email us at privacy@vividseats.com.
7. Children's Privacy
The Vivid Seats Marketplace is not directed to or intended to be used by individuals under the age of 16. We do not knowingly request or collect personal information from any person under 16 years of age without prior verifiable parental consent. If you believe that your child under the age of 16 has submitted personal information to us in connection with the Vivid Seats Marketplace, and without prior verifiable parental consent, please email us at privacy@vividseats.com so that we can take steps to delete the personal information that she or he has provided in accordance with applicable law.
8. Your Choices and Privacy
                        Rights
You have choices about how certain personal information is used and shared. Subject to applicable data protection law, you may have the right to request access to, correct, amend, delete and restrict the processing of your personal information. Where we rely on your consent to process your personal information, you have the right to withdraw your consent to our processing of your personal information at any time. You may also have the right to receive a copy of your personal information in a commonly used and machine-readable format and to transmit such data to another controller. To request deletion of, access to, or to make changes to personal information, or to otherwise exercise any of your rights in this paragraph, email us at privacy@vividseats.com. Please remember that if you delete or limit the use of your personal information, you may not be able to use the services provided through the Vivid Seats Marketplace.
Note that before completing your request, we may need additional information to verify your identity. We will send you a link to verify your email address and may request additional documentation or information solely for the purpose of verifying your identity. If you have an account with us, we will verify your identity through our existing authentication practices for your account.
Subject to applicable law, you may also designate, in writing or through a power of attorney document, an authorised agent to make requests on your behalf to exercise your rights. Before accepting such a request from an agent, we will require that the agent provide proof you have authorised them to act on your behalf, and we may need you to verify your identity directly with us. You may also have the right to appeal our decision regarding a request related to these rights by contacting us at privacy@vivideseats.com.
You also have the right to lodge a complaint with the supervisory authority in the country in which you live or work. If you live or work in the UK, you have the right to lodge a complaint with the
UK Information Commissioner’s Office
. If you live or work in the EU, a full list of EU supervisory authorities’ contact details is available
here
.
