9. Cookies and Other Tracking Technologies.
We, our affiliates and third parties use cookies such as Google Analytics in order to understand how you interact with the Vivid Seats Marketplace. If you wish to prevent your data from being used by Google Analytics, Google has developed the Google Analytics opt-out browser add-on available https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout/. Additionally, we, our affiliates and third parties may use other tracking technologies such as pixel tags, web beacons, SDKs, scripts and/or similar technologies on the Vivid Seats Marketplace and emails. As described further in the Privacy Preferences tool accessible via the footer of our Website, some of these cookies and similar technologies are necessary for the Website to function, while some optional technologies are used for certain functional purposes and to measure and analyze the performance of our ads on third party platforms. You can choose to decline all optional technologies in the Privacy Preferences tool accessible via the footer of our Website. You can also activate settings on your Internet browser to refuse the setting of some or all cookies, or take steps to remove existing cookies from your browser if you wish. Please keep in mind, however, that if you use your Internet browser settings to block all cookies (including essential/required cookies) you may not be able to access all or parts of the Vivid Seats Marketplace. For further information about managing cookies, please visit www.allaboutcookies.org. Please note that disabling or clearing cookies also may affect cookie-based opt-outs, including opt-outs set through our Privacy Preferences tool, by either preventing you from using such cookie-based opt-outs or clearing opt-outs that you have previously set, in which case you would have to revisit the applicable pages/tools and renew your opt-out after clearing cookies. In addition, our Website is not designed to respond to “Do Not Track” signals. Your mobile device may offer settings relating to cookies, pixel tags, SDKs, scripts and other similar technologies. We encourage to you to visit your device's help menu to learn about your options to limit tracking when using your device.
10. International Transfers
The Vivid Seats Marketplace is controlled and operated by Vivid Seats in the United States. To the extent that there is an international transfer of your personal data from the UK and EU to the United States in connection with your use of the Vivid Seats Marketplace, we rely on the
EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework
and/or the
UK-U.S. Data Bridge
(see more information on this below), or where applicable, appropriate safeguards such as standard contractual clauses. Similarly, we rely on adequacy decisions and appropriate safeguards to transfer your personal information to other countries outside the EU/UK, where applicable. Please contact us at
privacy@vividseats.com
for more information, or for a copy of the safeguards on which we rely.
11. Data Privacy Framework
We will treat all personal information subject to this Policy that is received from the EU, UK and Switzerland in accordance with Data Privacy Framework. Vivid Seats participates in the EU-U.S. Data Privacy Framework (the “EU-U.S. DPF”), the UK Extension to the EU-U.S. DPF and the Swiss-U.S. Data Privacy Framework and complies with the associated requirements regarding collection, use, and retention of personal information transferred from the EU, UK and Switzerland to the United States. Vivid Seats is subject to the investigatory and enforcement powers of the Federal Trade Commission and may be held liable in cases of onward transfers of data received from the EU, UK and Switzerland to third parties.
However, for the avoidance of doubt, Vivid Seats' adherence to the Data Privacy Frameworks does not apply to any human resources data. If there is any conflict between the terms in this Policy and the Data Privacy Framework Principles, the Data Privacy Framework Principles shall govern. To learn more about the Data Privacy Framework, and to see our certification, please visit https://www.dataprivacyframework.gov/s/.
Vivid Seats commits to resolve complaints about our collection or use of your personal information transferred to the U.S. pursuant to the Data Privacy Frameworks. EU, UK and Swiss individuals with Data Privacy Framework inquiries or complaints should first contact Vivid Seats at privacy@vividseats.com. If you do not receive timely acknowledgment of your complaint, or if your complaint is not satisfactorily addressed, please visit
https://www.dataprivacyframework.gov/s/article/How-to-Submit-a-Complaint-Relating-to-a-Participating-Organization-s-Compliance-with-the-DPF-Principles-dpf
for more information and to file a complaint. In the event you have a dispute or complaint with respect to your personal information, you are entitled to invoke binding arbitration, which may be referred to the International Centre for Dispute Resolution at the America Arbitration Association.
